com.googlecode.gwt.charts.client.query
Class QueryResponse

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      com.googlecode.gwt.charts.client.query.QueryResponse

public class QueryResponse
extends com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject

Represents a response of a query execution as received from the data source. An instance of this class is passed as an argument to the callback function that was set when Query.send was called.

Method Detail

getDataTable

public final DataTable getDataTable()
Returns the data table as returned by the data source. Returns null if the query execution failed and no data was returned.

Returns:
data table or null if query execution failed

getDetailedMessage

public final String getDetailedMessage()
Returns a detailed error message for queries that failed. If the query execution was successful, this method returns an empty string. The message returned is a message that is intended for developers, and may contain technical information, for example 'Column {salary} does not exist'.

Returns:
a detailed error message for queries that failed

getMessage

public final String getMessage()
Returns a short error message for queries that failed. If the query execution was successful, this method returns an empty string. The message returned is a short message that is intended for end users, for example 'Invalid Query' or 'Access Denied'.

Returns:
a short error message for queries that failed

getReasons

public final com.google.gwt.core.client.JsArrayString getReasons()
Returns an array of zero of more entries. Each entry is a short string with an error or warning code that was raised while executing the query. Possible codes:
  • access_denied The user does not have permissions to access the data source.
  • invalid_query The specified query has a syntax error.
  • data_truncated One or more data rows that match the query selection were not returned due to output size limits (warning).
  • timeout The query did not respond within the expected time.

Returns:
an array of error or warning codes

hasWarning

public final boolean hasWarning()
Returns true if the query execution has any warning messages.

Returns:
true if the query execution has any warning messages

isError

public final boolean isError()
Returns true if the query execution failed, and the response does not contain any data table. Returns false if the query execution was successful and the response contains a data table.

Returns:
true if the query execution failed, false otherwise
